0-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Daft-Punk@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/daft-punk">Daft Punk</a>的合作者托德·爱德华兹 (Todd Edwards) 表示，他相信两人“不再意见一致”。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/daft-punk-random-access-memories-get-lucky-10-hype-3429712">Daft Punk 的《Random Access Memories》发行 10 周年：它如何成为这个时代最受炒作的专辑</a></strong></li></ul><p>作为愚蠢朋克官方迷你纪录片<em>《Memory Tapes》</em>的最新嘉宾，该纪录片是为了庆祝他们的第四张也是最后一张专辑《Random Access Memories》发行 10 周年而制作的，爱德华兹说：“当他们分手时，他们已经进入了不同的状态。”方向，音乐。”</p><p>他继续说道：“Guy-Man[uel de Homem-Christo] 似乎更喜欢嘻哈领域，而<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/thomas-bangalter">Thomas [Bangalter]</a>也是一名导演。无论如何，感觉他们不再处于同一立场，所以我并不感到震惊。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Daft Punk - 记忆磁带 - 第 5 集 - 托德·爱德华兹（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0qpD-w7-DAE?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>爱德华兹首次与 Daft Punk 合作是在 2001 年，他们在二人组第二张 LP“Discovery”中的歌曲“Face to Face”中担任主唱并共同制作。然后，他在两人的第四张也是最后一张专辑“Random Access Memories”中的“Fragments Of Time”曲目中扮演了相同的角色。</p><p>在《傻朋克》结束时，爱德华兹建议其他音乐家不要哀悼他们不再是电子二人组，而应该从他们身上汲取灵感。</p><p> “我认为这对人们造成如此毁灭性的事实表明那里需要更多的傻朋克，”他说。 “如果说有什么不同的话，那就是它应该激励人们变得更有创造力，抓住机会，停止做同样的事情，永远谨慎行事。”</p><p>在其他新闻中，班加特透露，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/thomas-bangalter-relieved-over-way-daft-punk-ended-3478342">对《愚蠢朋克》的结束方式感到“松了一口气”</a> 。</p><p>在与<a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0017kqb" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BBC Radio 6 Music</a>的讨论中，Bangalter 解释说，结束这个项目“感觉很好”，有时也会对 Daft Punk 在 1997 年首张专辑<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/daft-punk-release-25th-anniversary-edition-of-debut-album-3167260">“Homework”之后继续创作音乐的时间感到惊讶。</a></p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/daft-punk-werent-on-the-same-page-anymore-says-collaborator-todd-edwards-3495227">合作者托德·爱德华兹 (Todd Edwards) 表示，《傻朋克》的帖子“不再在同一页上”，</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner) 通过现场表演解释了对抗有毒男性气质的重要性https://www.nme.com/news/music/loyle-carner-explains-the-importance-of-combating-有毒-masculinity-with-his-live-shows-3495208?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=loyle-卡纳解释了用他的现场表演对抗有毒男子气概的重要性Liberty DunworthFri, 08 Sep 2023 14:51:07 +0000 Music InterviewsMusic NewsNewsHip-hop https://www.nme.com/?p=3495208 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="2023 年 9 月 7 日，英国伦敦，洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner) 在 Eventim Apollo 举行的 2023 年水星奖颁奖典礼上登台表演。" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我认为给孩子们这样说话的地方，尤其是年轻人，很重要”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/loyle-carner-explains-the-importance-of-combating-toxic-masculinity-with-his-live-shows-3495208">Loyle Carner 的帖子解释了对抗有毒男性气质的重要性，他的现场表演</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="2023 年 9 月 7 日，英国伦敦，洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner) 在 Eventim Apollo 举行的 2023 年水星奖颁奖典礼上登台表演。" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/loyle-carner">洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner)</a>公开了利用他的现场表演来反对有毒的男子气概的重要性，并回顾了自首张专辑以来他如何成长。查看上面的完整采访。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/loyle-carner-hugo-review-an-honest-unflashy-storyteller-3332632">洛伊尔·卡纳（Loyle Carner）——《雨果》评论：一个诚实、不浮夸的讲故事的人</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p>这位英国嘻哈歌手兼词曲作家在今年水星奖的红地毯上采访了<em>《NME》</em> ，并回顾了今年早些时候他在<a href="https://www.nme.com/reading-festival-2023">雷丁和利兹</a>举行的大型演出。</p><p>在这里，这位入围艺术家回顾了他上个月在主舞台上的表演，并透露了为什么他将大部分时间都花在抵制有害态度上。</p><p> “这太神奇了，伙计，”他开始说道，解释了在他的现场演出中产生如此积极的反应是什么感觉。 “我觉得演出结束后的谈话中，那些小细节最重要。就像孩子们说‘谢谢’一样。”</p><p>卡纳还回忆起演出结束后有人联系他，告诉他他感人的表演鼓励她的儿子站出来开始讨论心理健康问题。</p><p> “我在 Instagram 上收到了一位妈妈发来的一条美丽的信息，说她的儿子经历了一些事情。我不需要透露这一点，但这是他第一次能够对她说‘哟，我经历过，这伤害了我’，”艺术家补充道。 “我认为给孩子们一个这样说话的地方——尤其是年轻人，因为在我长大的时候这是不允许的——这很重要。” </p><figure id="attachment_3495226" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3495226" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3495226" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270.jpg" alt="洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner) 于 2023 年 9 月 7 日在英国伦敦举办的 Eventim Apollo 2023 年水星奖颁奖典礼上登台表演" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-live-2@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3495226" class="wp-caption-text"> 2023 年 9 月 7 日，英国伦敦，洛伊尔·卡纳 (Loyle Carner) 在 Eventim Apollo 举行的 2023 年水星奖颁奖典礼上登台表演。图片来源：JMEnternational/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>他继续说道：“这很有趣，伙计，那个视频被发布在 Instagram 的某个[页面]上……而且上面的评论非常有毒。说这些关于我的废话，我应该闭嘴……这让我意识到说这个[信息]是多么重要，因为那些孩子和我一样迷失了。”</p><p> Elsewhere in this discussion with <em>NME</em> , Carner also revealed how he has evolved as an artist, and noticed a change between his latest album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/loyle-carner-hugo-review-an-honest-unflashy-storyteller-3332632">&#39;Hugo&#39;</a> and his 2017 debut <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/loyle-carner-yesterdays-gone-review-1959441">&#39;Yesterday&#39;s Gone&#39;</a> .</p><p> Both albums saw the musician shortlisted for the Mercury Prize, however, this time around he said was able to attend the ceremony with a wider sense of clarity, and able enjoy the milestone more than before.</p><p> “I guess every time you&#39;re making an album, you&#39;re making it in response to the one that you&#39;ve just made before. I think that&#39;s been true of what I&#39;ve made up to this point,” he said. “I feel like I&#39;m able to take myself less seriously [than in 2017, especially] when it comes to stuff like this, which means I&#39;m able to enjoy stuff more.”</p><p> “I&#39;m also a father now. I get less sleep — that&#39;s how I&#39;m different! I&#39;m knackered all the time. That&#39;s the real difference,” he continued, going on to share his admiration for other shortlisted artists this year. </p><figure id="attachment_3495231" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3495231" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3495231" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Loyle Carner performs onstage during The Mercury Prize 2023 awards show at Eventim Apollo on September 07, 2023 in London, England." width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Loyle-Carner-Mercury@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3495231" class="wp-caption-text"> Loyle Carner performs onstage during The Mercury Prize 2023 awards show at Eventim Apollo on September 07, 2023 in London, England.</figcaption></figure><p> “It&#39;s deep, because, when I came in before, I felt like an outsider looking in, you know?<br /> What I loved about being here last time was like feeling part of the conversation. That&#39;s all I ever wanted, just to be in and amongst something.</p><p> “That&#39;s deep for me because these are people I really respect — <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ezra-collective">Ezra Collective</a> , those are my guys. <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/olivia-dean">Olivia Dean</a> , I love so much. <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/young-fathers">Young Fathers</a> , I never really chatted to but I&#39;m a big fan. So to be around these people [like] <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shygirl">Shygirl</a> , it&#39;s sick for me.”</p><p> Carner&#39;s third album &#39;Hugo&#39; arrived last October, and in <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/loyle-carner-hugo-review-an-honest-unflashy-storyteller-3332632">a four-star review</a> , <em>NME</em> described the release as “his most polished record yet”.</p><p> “Carner move[s] from dynamic, multi-syllabic storytelling to a more honest, reflective voice,” it read. “It&#39;s personal, yet far-reaching; the rapper mourns his father, but he also mourns strangers, kids lost to violence, crime, a hostile state. He&#39;s sorrowful, fully aware of the injustice of the world, but more at ease with his place within it.”</p><p> Elsewhere at the Mercury Prize this year, British jazz band <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ezra-collective-win-the-2023-mercury-prize-for-where-im-meant-to-be-3494841">Ezra Collective took home the coveted award</a> – beating off competition from the likes of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/RAYE">Raye</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/young-fathers">Young Fathers</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ARCTIC-MONKEYS">Arctic Monkeys</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lankum">Lankum</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shygirl">Shygirl</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jockstrap">Jockstrap</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/JESSIE-WARE">Jessie Ware</a> .</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ezra-collective-on-their-impact-on-the-jazz-scene-and-plans-to-celebrate-their-mercury-prize-win-3495161">Speaking with <em>NME</em></a> , the band&#39;s drummer Femi Koleoso explained what it meant for Ezra Collective to be representing the jazz community at the prestigious award ceremony, saying it was “wonderful to be a part of something so big and so special”.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/loyle-carner-explains-the-importance-of-combating-toxic-masculinity-with-his-live-shows-3495208">Loyle Carner explains the importance of combating toxic masculinity with his live shows</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
